
[1]perspicuity

   PERSPICU'ITY, n. [L. perspicuitas, from perspicio.]

   1. Transparency; clearness; that quality of a substance which renders
   objects visible through it. [Little used.]

   2. Clearness to mental vision; easiness to be understood; freedom from
   obscurity or ambiguity; that quality of writing or language which
   readily presents to the mind of another the precise ideas of the
   author. Perspicuity is the first excellence of writing or speaking.
